    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-12T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-12T04:00:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9300: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Canton</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Linnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-12T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 12, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 12—8:18 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following from Ketcham,<note n="83" xml:id="d422fn83">John B. Ketcham, Consul at
                        Swatow.</note> Swatow.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“August 12, 1 p.m. Japanese Consul is leaving this afternoon. Japanese
                        Consulate turned over to Chinese police for protection. Remaining <pb
                            facs="0391" n="384" xml:id="pg_384"/> Japanese are evacuating this
                        afternoon but Japanese Consul informed me about 70 Formosans are remaining
                        in Swatow. Japanese Consul states that his departure is due to increasing
                        anti-Japanese [campaign?] but that Japanese Navy will not take action if
                        Chinese do not attack naval vessels, Japanese subjects or property.
                        Department has not been informed”.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Sent to the Department, Peiping, Nanking and by mail to Shanghai, Hong Kong,
                    Amoy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Linnell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
